<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Fable</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-11 12:16:09</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Hi all,<BR>
I am a Dark Elf Magician and have just finally completed the full quest for the Mystic Cloak. To clear up some of the questions on this board about the quest here's how a DE CAN do the quest with time and patience.<BR>
The Preist of Najena is an "Area effected Spawn" he spawns in the little torture area up the side stairs in Unrest (the exact coordinates are given in a post on the first page of messages). Kill the usual ghoul placeholder and then go sit at the bottom of the stairs by the door. DO NOT go on the stairs or allow anyone to go up them. Wait his 56 minutes spawn time and if everyone keeps off the stairs he will pop EVERY time. To prove my point I have had him pop 3 times in a row to show people this does actually work. Get the key he drops.<BR>
Now you go to Cazic and obtain TWO potions of Clay Golem.<BR>
Once having the potions avaliable you go to the jails in Najena. Use one potion to transform into an earth elemental and hand the key to Linara parlone (high elf chanter) STAY away from the injured halfing also in the same cell he CAN see thru the illusion! You take the letter Linara gives you and head via a druid friend (lvl 39+ for wolf form) to felwith.<BR>
Invis to pass the guards at Felwith entrance and once you zone into felwith do NOT move off the zone line, have your druid friend wolf you immediatley. There is a guard above the zone line who will aggro if you step forward without it and you dont always see him. Now head to the waters edge and the father (Parlone) is the High elf on the right hand side, hand him the letter and get the faded Cloak.<BR>
Now you head to Erudin.<BR>
The fun and games start here, this is what I had to do to complete the quest.....Earth elementals are KOS to the Palace guards (go figure!) so my Druid friend went up to the chanter guild and found Linara's Mother (also last name Parlone) aggro'd her and took her to the crystal port out of the palace. I waited invis down a set of steps to the side while he zoned out healed and came back, he then snared the 4 guards wandering around that area and ran them around for a minute while I transformed into elemental form handed the Faded claok over and zoned out immediatly (with sow) and headed for the tox zone at a rapid rate hehehhe.<BR>
<BR>
Anyways I am now a KOS Dark ELf with the rather nice Mystic Cloak which happily put me to 200 Intelligence.<BR>
And thats how a DE does the quest =) If anyone wants to see it for prove, come to the Rathe, will be happy for you to inspect me anytime =)<BR>
<BR>
Fable Mysticweaver - The Rathe<BR>
Magician of the 30th achivement</font></td></tr></table>
